<introduction>
<p>
  Show that $y(x)=\frac{x(x-1)}{x^3-27}$ has
</p>
</introduction>
<task>
<statement>
<p>
 both a global and a local minimum if its domain is the
    interval $(-5,0)$, and
  </p>
</statement>
</task>
