<p>
 Does the graph of this function have a global maximum for
    either of the domains given in parts (a) or (b)? Explain.
  </p>
</statement>
</task>
</problem>
<!-- \begin{embeddedproblem-1line}  -->
<!--   Show that $y(x)=\frac{x(x-1)}{x^3-27}$ has -->
